text: The Crown of Ireland Act 1542 (33 Henry 8 c.1) was an act passed by the Irish Parliament during the reign of Henry VIII, King of England and Lord of Ireland that elevated the island from a lordship to the status of a kingdom. ==References== Category:History of Ireland Category:1542 Category:1540s in Europe Category:History of the United Kingdom Category:Politics of Northern Ireland
title: Crown of Ireland Act 1542
